  "texts": [
    "The encoder, located on the left side of U-Net, uses convolutional layers and max pooling layers to compress the spatial dimensions of the input image and extract significant features.",
    "The down sampling process generates perceptions and features in a hierarchical manner.",
    "The decoder (right side of the U-Net) uses transposed convolutions to up sample these features to the original image size.",
    "The decoder then employs skip connections to concatenate these features with the corresponding encoder's feature maps.",
    "By using these bypass connections, U-Net is able to incorporate both high-level and low-level features that are crucial for localization."
  ],
